sonaqube is a code quality analysyi tool 
the default port is 900o
sonarqube needs at least 4gig ram 
install java mostly 1.8 ,  yum install java-1.8* on a linux/redhat/ instance 
import sonar.repo either by using ;
wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/sonar.repo http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/sonar-pkg/rpm/sonar.repo 

OR 

create a file in /etc/yum.repos.d -- that is where the repos needs to be and add 
[sonar]
name=Sonar
baseurl=http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/sonar-pkg/rpm
gpgcheck=0

both steps worrk 

next install sonar , yum/dnf install sonar 

start sonar service with  *service sonar start* and you can verify it works 


